fashions of 1934 is a 1934 american pre-code musical comedy film directed by william dieterle with musical numbers created and directed by busby berkeley . the screenplay by f. hugh herbert and carl erickson was based on the story the fashion plate by harry collins and warren duff . the film stars william powell , bette davis , hugh herbert and frank mchugh , and has songs by sammy fain ( music ) and irving &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ( lyrics ) . ( sometime after the initial release , the title " fashions of 1934 " was changed to " fashions " , replacing the original title with an insert card stating william powell in " fashions " ) .